Godot master, Windows 10 64 bits

Passing a reference to a GDNative class to the method of another GDNative class doesn't work.

I created two C++ classes in a GDNative library, with the following setup, simplified:

```cpp
class A : public Reference {

	void _init() {
		m_seed = 131183;
	}

	int get_seed() {
		return m_seed;
	}

	int m_seed;
};

class B : public Reference {

	void set_a(A * a) {
		a->reference();
		m_a = a;
	}

	A * m_a;
};
```

And used in GDScript the following way:

```gdscript
func _ready():
	var a = A.new()
	var b = B.new()
	b.set_a(a)
```

Problem: when the reference to A comes into B, it points to some kind of "ghost" instance where `seed` is 0, not 131183. In my actual project I also have a pointer in that class which makes it crash because it's garbage.
